comments: Matthews (MIL) reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball defending Brown (BOS).
Smart (BOS) makes contact to Antetokounmpo's (MIL) arm that affects his shot attempt at the basket.
Middleton (MIL) legally contests White's (BOS) jump shot attempt.
Williams (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position as he absorbs the marginal contact initiated by Holiday (MIL) during the driving shot attempt.
Portis (MIL) legally contests Brown's (BOS) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.

After Brown (BOS) misses the jump shot attempt, play is blown dead at the 00:43.3 mark because there is doubt if the shot hit the rim.  After communicating with the Replay Center, it is confirmed that the ball did not hit the rim and the shot clock should not have been reset during play.  The shot clock is reset to 7 seconds remaining and the game clock remains at 00:43.3.  The shot clock should have been reset to 11 seconds remaining and the game clock to 00:47.0, the point at which Williams (BOS) possesses the rebound.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) makes marginal contact with Theis' (BOS) lower body during his shot near the rim.
Brown (BOS) commits a take foul on Antetokounmpo (MIL).
Theis (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Matthews (MIL) and does not deliver contact.
Brown (BOS) dribbles the ball off of Hill's (MIL) foot and he does not intentionally kick the ball.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of a defensive goaltending by Theis (BOS) is confirmed.
Middleton (MIL) does not attain frontcourt status before making the pass to Holiday (MIL) and is still considered in the backcourt.
